#. <section class="sutta" id="sn35.53"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn35.53:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 35"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 35"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.53:0.2"
msgid "6. Avijjāvagga"
msgstr "6. Ignorance"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 53. Avijjāpahānasutta → avijjā (pts1)
msgctxt "sn35.53:0.3"
msgid "53. Avijjāpahānasutta"
msgstr "53. Giving Up Ignorance"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi4.31"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.53:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ."
msgstr "At Sāvatthī."

msgctxt "sn35.53:1.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho aññataro bhikkhu yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā "
"bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho so bhikkhu "
"bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"Then a mendicant went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and "
"said to him:"

msgctxt "sn35.53:1.3"
msgid ""
"“kathaṃ nu kho, bhante, jānato kathaṃ passato avijjā pahīyati, vijjā "
"uppajjatī”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“Sir, how does one know and see so as to give up ignorance and give rise to "
"knowledge?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.53:2.1"
msgid ""
"“Cakkhuṃ kho, bhikkhu, aniccato jānato passato avijjā pahīyati, vijjā "
"uppajjati."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicant, knowing and seeing the eye, sights, eye consciousness, and eye "
"contact as impermanent, ignorance is given up and knowledge arises."

msgctxt "sn35.53:2.2"
msgid "Rūpe aniccato jānato passato avijjā pahīyati, vijjā uppajjati."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn35.53:2.3"
msgid "Cakkhuviññāṇaṃ …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn35.53:2.4"
msgid "cakkhusamphassaṃ …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn35.53:2.5"
msgid ""
"yampidaṃ cakkhusamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedayitaṃ sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā "
"adukkhamasukhaṃ vā tampi aniccato jānato passato avijjā pahīyati, vijjā "
"uppajjati."
msgstr ""
"And also knowing and seeing the pleasant, painful, or neutral feeling that "
"arises conditioned by eye contact as impermanent, ignorance is given up and "
"knowledge arises."

msgctxt "sn35.53:2.6"
msgid "Sotaṃ …"
msgstr "Knowing and seeing the ear …"

msgctxt "sn35.53:2.7"
msgid "ghānaṃ …"
msgstr "nose …"

msgctxt "sn35.53:2.8"
msgid "jivhaṃ …"
msgstr "tongue …"

msgctxt "sn35.53:2.9"
msgid "kāyaṃ …"
msgstr "body …"

msgctxt "sn35.53:2.10"
msgid "manaṃ aniccato jānato passato avijjā pahīyati, vijjā uppajjati."
msgstr ""
"Knowing and seeing the mind, thoughts, mind consciousness, and mind contact "
"as impermanent, ignorance is given up and knowledge arises."

msgctxt "sn35.53:2.11"
msgid "Dhamme …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn35.53:2.12"
msgid "manoviññāṇaṃ …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn35.53:2.13"
msgid "manosamphassaṃ …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn35.53:2.14"
msgid ""
"yampidaṃ manosamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedayitaṃ sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā "
"adukkhamasukhaṃ vā tampi aniccato jānato passato avijjā pahīyati, vijjā "
"uppajjati."
msgstr ""
"And also knowing and seeing the pleasant, painful, or neutral feeling that "
"arises conditioned by mind contact as impermanent, ignorance is given up and "
"knowledge arises."

msgctxt "sn35.53:2.15"
msgid ""
"Evaṃ kho, bhikkhu, jānato evaṃ passato avijjā pahīyati, vijjā uppajjatī”ti."
msgstr ""
"That’s how to know and see so as to give up ignorance and give rise to "
"knowledge.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn35.53:2.16"
msgid "Paṭhamaṃ."
msgstr ""
